(
  'what-are-nicotine-pouches',
  'What Are Nicotine Pouches? A Complete Guide',
  'Everything you need to know about nicotine pouches — what they are, how they work, and why they are rapidly replacing traditional snus across Europe.',
  E'## What Are Nicotine Pouches?\n\nNicotine pouches are small, pre-portioned pouches containing nicotine, plant-based fibres, flavourings, and sweeteners. Unlike traditional snus, they contain **no tobacco leaf whatsoever**. You place one between your upper lip and gum, and the nicotine is absorbed through the oral mucosa over 15 to 45 minutes.\n\nSince launching in Scandinavia around 2016, nicotine pouches have exploded in popularity. Today they are available in dozens of countries and come in hundreds of flavour and strength combinations.\n\n## How Do They Work?\n\nWhen a pouch sits against your gum, moisture activates the nicotine and flavour. You will usually feel a mild tingling sensation — this is normal and fades after a few minutes. Most users keep a pouch in for 20 to 40 minutes, though some prefer shorter or longer sessions depending on the strength.\n\nThere is nothing to spit, no smoke, and no vapour. This makes nicotine pouches one of the most discreet ways to consume nicotine.\n\n## Tobacco-Free vs Traditional Snus\n\nTraditional Swedish snus is made from ground tobacco packed under the lip. It has been used in Scandinavia for over two centuries and has a strong cultural following. However, snus is banned for sale in most EU countries outside Sweden.\n\nNicotine pouches sidestep this restriction because they contain no tobacco. The nicotine is either extracted from the tobacco plant and purified, or in some cases synthesised. This distinction matters for regulation, taxation, and — for many users — personal preference.\n\n**Key differences at a glance:**\n\n- **Staining:** Snus can stain teeth over time; white nicotine pouches do not.\n- **Taste:** Snus has an earthy, tobacco-forward flavour. Pouches come in mint, citrus, berry, coffee, and many more.\n- **Regulations:** Nicotine pouches are legal across the EU; snus is restricted to Sweden.\n- **Nicotine delivery:** Both deliver nicotine through the gum, but absorption speed can vary by product.\n\n## Who Uses Nicotine Pouches?\n\nThe user base is broad. Former smokers looking for a smokeless alternative, existing snus users wanting a tobacco-free option, and adults who simply prefer a discreet nicotine experience. The category skews younger than traditional snus, partly because of the wider flavour range and modern branding.\n\n## Are They Safe?\n\nNo nicotine product is risk-free. Nicotine is addictive, and pouches are intended for adults only. That said, because nicotine pouches contain no tobacco and involve no combustion, they avoid the tar, carbon monoxide, and many of the carcinogens associated with smoking. Long-term independent studies are still ongoing.\n\n## Getting Started\n\nIf you are new to nicotine pouches, start with a lower strength (2 to 6 mg) and a flavour you find appealing. Place the pouch under your upper lip, let it sit, and remove it when the flavour fades. Browse our [shop](/shop) to explore brands and strengths, or check out our guide on [choosing the right nicotine strength](/blog/how-to-choose-nicotine-strength).',
  'SnusFriend Team',
  ARRAY['guide', 'beginners'],
  true,
  now(),
  'What Are Nicotine Pouches? A Complete Guide | SnusFriend',
  'Learn what nicotine pouches are, how they work, and how they differ from traditional snus. A comprehensive guide for beginners and experienced users alike.'
),
(
  'how-to-choose-nicotine-strength',
  'How to Choose Your Nicotine Strength',
  'Not sure which nicotine strength to pick? This guide breaks down the different levels so you can find the perfect match for your experience and preferences.',
  E'## Finding Your Ideal Nicotine Strength\n\nNicotine pouches come in a wide range of strengths, typically measured in milligrams per pouch. Choosing the right level is one of the most important decisions for a satisfying experience — too low and you will not feel much, too high and it can be uncomfortable.\n\n## The Strength Tiers\n\n### Low (2–4 mg)\nIdeal for complete beginners or those who want a very gentle nicotine experience. If you have never used nicotine before, start here. The sensation is subtle and the tingling is minimal.\n\n### Medium (6–8 mg)\nThe most popular range for everyday users. This is where most people settle after trying a few options. It provides a noticeable but comfortable nicotine hit without being overwhelming. Former light smokers often find this range satisfying.\n\n### Strong (10–14 mg)\nDesigned for experienced users or former heavy smokers. The nicotine kick is pronounced and the tingling can be intense for the first few minutes. If you are transitioning from strong snus or heavy smoking, this range may feel familiar.\n\n### Extra Strong (16 mg+)\nThese are for seasoned nicotine users only. Brands like Pablo and Siberia push into the 20–30 mg range. The experience is intense and not recommended for beginners under any circumstances. Even experienced users should approach these with respect.\n\n## How to Find Your Level\n\n- **Start low.** It is always easier to move up than to recover from a too-strong pouch.\n- **Give it time.** Use a strength for at least a few days before deciding it is too weak. Your body adjusts.\n- **Consider your history.** Non-smokers should start at 2–4 mg. Former pack-a-day smokers might be comfortable at 8–10 mg.\n- **Check the brand.** A "strong" pouch from one brand might feel different from another. Nicotine delivery depends on pouch size, moisture, pH, and filler material.\n- **Listen to your body.** Hiccups, nausea, or dizziness mean the strength is too high. Remove the pouch and try a lower level next time.\n\n## A Quick Reference\n\n| Experience Level | Recommended Strength | Examples |\n|---|---|---|\n| Never used nicotine | 2–4 mg | ZYN Mini Dry 1.5 mg, VELO 4 mg |\n| Light smoker / casual | 6–8 mg | ZYN 6 mg, Loop Mint 6.5 mg |\n| Regular smoker / snus user | 10–14 mg | VELO 10 mg, White Fox 12 mg |\n| Heavy user | 16 mg+ | Pablo 16 mg, Siberia 24 mg |\n\nRemember, there is no "correct" strength — only what works for you. Browse our [shop](/shop) to explore different options and find your match.',
  'SnusFriend Team',
  ARRAY['guide', 'beginners', 'nicotine-strength'],
  true,
  now(),
  'How to Choose Your Nicotine Strength | SnusFriend',
  'A beginner-friendly guide to nicotine pouch strengths — from low (2-4 mg) to extra strong (16 mg+). Find the right level for your experience.'
),
(
  'top-nicotine-pouch-brands-2026',
  'Top 10 Nicotine Pouch Brands in 2026',
  'From ZYN to Killa, here are the ten nicotine pouch brands leading the market in 2026 — with what makes each one stand out.',
  E'## The Best Nicotine Pouch Brands Right Now\n\nThe nicotine pouch market has matured significantly over the past few years. With dozens of brands competing for shelf space, it can be hard to know where to start. Here are the ten brands defining the category in 2026.\n\n## 1. ZYN\nThe undisputed market leader. Made by Swedish Match (now part of Philip Morris International), ZYN pioneered the modern nicotine pouch and remains the best-selling brand globally. Known for consistent quality, a wide strength range, and classic flavours like Spearmint and Citrus. Available almost everywhere.\n\n## 2. VELO\nBritish American Tobacco''s answer to ZYN. VELO (formerly LYFT in some markets) offers a premium feel with slim, comfortable pouches. Their flavour range is extensive — from Ice Cool to Ruby Berry — and the branding is sleek. Particularly strong in Europe.\n\n## 3. Loop\nA Swedish brand that stands out for its unique "Instant" and "Flow" technology, which controls how quickly flavour and nicotine are released. Loop''s Jalapeho Lime and Red Chili Melon flavours show they are not afraid to experiment.\n\n## 4. White Fox\nKnown for its striking packaging and strong mint flavours. White Fox keeps things simple — fewer flavour options but each one is executed well. Their Full Charge variant is a favourite among users who prefer a powerful kick.\n\n## 5. Skruf\nA heritage Swedish brand that transitioned from traditional snus to tobacco-free pouches under the "Skruf Super White" line. Skruf brings decades of Scandinavian craftsmanship to the category. Their Cassice (blackcurrant) flavour is a cult favourite.\n\n## 6. LYFT\nWhile LYFT was rebranded to VELO in many markets, the LYFT name persists in several countries and still carries a loyal following. The product is identical to VELO in most cases, but some regional flavour exclusives keep the brand alive.\n\n## 7. Pablo\nThe brand synonymous with extreme strength. Pablo''s flagship products push past 20 mg per pouch, making them a go-to for users who want maximum intensity. Not for beginners, but hugely popular in the strong-pouch community.\n\n## 8. 77\nA no-nonsense brand offering good quality at a competitive price. 77 pouches are slim, comfortable, and come in straightforward flavours like Cherry, Cola, and Blueberry. A solid everyday option without the premium price tag.\n\n## 9. Sting\nA newer entrant that has gained traction thanks to bold flavours and eye-catching tins. Sting positions itself for a younger adult audience with tropical flavour profiles and strong social-media presence.\n\n## 10. Killa\nAnother high-strength brand with a loyal following. Killa pouches are moist, flavourful, and deliver a fast nicotine hit. Their Cold Mint and Watermelon variants are bestsellers. Like Pablo, Killa is aimed at experienced users who know their limits.\n\n## How to Choose\n\nEach brand has its personality. If you want reliable consistency, start with ZYN or VELO. If you prefer adventurous flavours, try Loop. If strength is your priority, Pablo and Killa have you covered. Explore our [shop](/shop) to compare options and find your favourites.',
  'SnusFriend Team',
  ARRAY['brands', 'reviews'],
  true,
  now(),
  'Top 10 Nicotine Pouch Brands in 2026 | SnusFriend',
  'Discover the best nicotine pouch brands of 2026 — ZYN, VELO, Loop, White Fox, Skruf, and more. Brief reviews and what makes each brand unique.'
),
(
  'nicotine-pouches-vs-snus',
  'Nicotine Pouches vs Traditional Snus: What''s the Difference?',
  'Nicotine pouches and traditional snus both go under the lip, but they are fundamentally different products. Here is how they compare.',
  E'## Two Products, One Placement\n\nIf you have heard of snus, you might wonder how nicotine pouches are any different. After all, both are small pouches that sit under the upper lip. But beneath the surface, these are distinct products with different ingredients, regulations, and user experiences.\n\n## What Is Traditional Snus?\n\nSnus is a moist tobacco product that originated in Sweden in the 18th century. It is made from air-dried or steam-pasteurised ground tobacco, salt, water, and flavourings. Snus comes in loose form (which you shape by hand) or pre-portioned pouches. It has a distinctive earthy, tobacco-forward taste.\n\nSweden has one of the lowest smoking rates in Europe, and many researchers attribute this partly to snus being a culturally accepted alternative.\n\n## What Are Nicotine Pouches?\n\nNicotine pouches contain **no tobacco**. Instead, they use plant-based fibres (often from eucalyptus or pine) as a base, combined with purified nicotine, flavourings, sweeteners, and pH adjusters. They are always pre-portioned and come in white or nearly white pouches.\n\n## Key Differences\n\n### Tobacco Content\nThis is the fundamental distinction. Snus contains tobacco; nicotine pouches do not. This affects taste, colour, regulation, and how each product is perceived.\n\n### Teeth Staining\nTraditional snus — especially the darker loose varieties — can stain teeth over time. Nicotine pouches are white and do not cause staining, which is one of the top reasons users switch.\n\n### Flavour Profile\nSnus has a natural tobacco taste that some users love and others find off-putting. Nicotine pouches come in virtually every flavour imaginable: mint, citrus, berry, coffee, cola, tropical fruits, and even spicy options.\n\n### Legal Status\nSnus is banned for sale in all EU countries except Sweden (where it has a cultural exemption). Nicotine pouches, because they are tobacco-free, are legal across the EU, though regulations on strength and marketing vary by country.\n\n### Drip and Spit\nSnus can produce more saliva, and some users spit (though most Swedish users swallow). Nicotine pouches tend to produce less drip, making them more discreet.\n\n### Shelf Life\nSnus must be refrigerated for optimal freshness. Nicotine pouches are shelf-stable and can be stored at room temperature without degradation.\n\n## Which Should You Choose?\n\nIf you enjoy the taste of tobacco and live in Sweden, traditional snus remains an excellent option with a long track record. If you prefer variety, want to avoid staining, or live outside Sweden, nicotine pouches are the practical choice.\n\nMany users start with snus and transition to pouches for convenience. Others go straight to pouches without ever trying snus. There is no wrong answer — it comes down to personal preference.\n\nExplore both categories in our [shop](/shop) and see what suits you best.',
  'SnusFriend Team',
  ARRAY['guide', 'snus', 'comparison'],
  true,
  now(),
  'Nicotine Pouches vs Traditional Snus: What''s the Difference? | SnusFriend',
  'A clear comparison of nicotine pouches and traditional snus — covering tobacco content, staining, flavours, legal status, and which is right for you.'
),
(
  'tips-for-first-time-users',
  '5 Tips for First-Time Nicotine Pouch Users',
  'New to nicotine pouches? These five practical tips will help you get the best experience from your very first pouch.',
  E'## Your First Pouch — Make It Count\n\nTrying nicotine pouches for the first time can be a little daunting. What strength should you pick? Where exactly does it go? How long do you leave it in? Here are five tips to make your introduction as smooth as possible.\n\n## 1. Start With a Low Strength\n\nThis is the single most important piece of advice. If you have never used nicotine, begin with 2 to 4 mg. If you are a former smoker, 4 to 6 mg is a reasonable starting point. You can always move up — but a first experience with an overly strong pouch can put people off entirely.\n\nThe tingling sensation is normal, especially with mint flavours. It should feel pleasant, not painful. If you feel nauseous or dizzy, the strength is too high.\n\n## 2. Get the Placement Right\n\nTuck the pouch between your upper lip and gum, slightly off-centre. Most people prefer the left or right side rather than dead centre. The upper lip is standard because the gum tissue there absorbs nicotine effectively and the pouch stays in place without much effort.\n\nAvoid moving the pouch around with your tongue — let it sit. After a minute or two, you will barely notice it is there.\n\n## 3. Mind the Duration\n\nA typical session lasts 20 to 40 minutes. You will notice the flavour fading toward the end, which is a natural sign to remove it. Some people prefer shorter sessions of 10 to 15 minutes, especially when starting out.\n\nThere is no strict rule, but leaving a pouch in for over an hour is unnecessary and can irritate the gum. Listen to your body.\n\n## 4. Stay Hydrated\n\nNicotine is a mild diuretic, and the pouch itself absorbs some moisture from your mouth. Keep water nearby, especially during your first few sessions. Staying hydrated also helps with the tingling and keeps the experience comfortable.\n\nAvoid using nicotine pouches on an empty stomach if you are new to nicotine — it can amplify the effects and cause lightheadedness.\n\n## 5. Explore Different Flavours\n\nOne of the best things about nicotine pouches is the variety. If your first flavour does not click, do not write off the entire category. Mint and citrus are the most popular starting points, but there are dozens of options — from berry and tropical to coffee and liquorice.\n\nMany brands sell mixed packs or smaller tins specifically for newcomers. Take advantage of these to find what you enjoy before committing to a full roll.\n\n## Bonus: Disposal\n\nMost tins have a compartment in the lid for used pouches. Pop the spent pouch in there and dispose of it in a bin later. Never litter — pouches are not biodegradable and take years to break down.\n\n## Ready to Start?\n\nBrowse our [shop](/shop) for beginner-friendly options, or read our [nicotine strength guide](/blog/how-to-choose-nicotine-strength) for more detail on finding the right level. Welcome to the community!',
  'SnusFriend Team',
  ARRAY['guide', 'beginners', 'tips'],
  true,
  now(),
  '5 Tips for First-Time Nicotine Pouch Users | SnusFriend',
  'Practical advice for nicotine pouch beginners — from choosing your first strength to placement, duration, and finding your favourite flavour.'
)
ON CONFLICT (slug) DO NOTHING;
